Description:
JOB DETAILS
Office Location:
Victoria, BC
We would love to have you join us at our HQ office in beautiful Victoria, BC and will provide relocation assistance no matter where in the world you currently live.
We are
completely remote-friendly
- you do not have to work in the office every day. However this role will have responsibilities that regularly require a physical presence in Victoria and in our office.
THE ROLE
We're growing faster than a pimple on picture day and need your help to further develop and execute our marketing and communications strategy. As you activate the internal marketing plan for our organization you will create digital media, direct content production, improve our sales collateral, and increase our brand awareness through our website, social media, and other earned media opportunities. Ultimately your goals are to:
Increase positive sentiment for our brand (internally and externally);
Generate inbound leads, and;
Help nurture the relationships with our clients and partners.
You will have the support of designers, writers, analysts, developers and our growth team to achieve the ambitious objectives you will help us create as you build a career here.
As an experienced marketing professional, you have outstanding written and verbal communication skills. You are comfortable working with your teammates across the organization as well as our clients, our event guests, media representatives, and contractors or vendors. You will need strong organizational skills - if you've ever built a spreadsheet to plan a housewarming party, you're on the right track. You thrive in a fast-paced environment and don't crack under pressure. You are ambitious, and want to work at a sustainable pace towards high impact and high quality results on projects you have owned from start to finish.
KEY RESPONSIBILITIES
Within your first month you will be able to...
Understand and be able to effectively communicate our mission, vision, values, and guiding principles in company announcements or internal communications;
Help prepare our monthly Company Check-in (all hands meeting) with input from our 4 business pillars (Growth, People Ops, Service Delivery, and Technology);
Understand the processes and best practices to produce and share a piece of marketing content (eg. blog post or digital portfolio);
Perform SEO on a recent blog post and schedule the next month's social posts for sharing with our public sector audiences in mind;
Update our Sales and Marketing KPI Dashboard by gathering and analyzing data from multiple sources.
Within your first 90 days you will be able to...
Research, write, create, and publish a new case study on our website every 1-2 months;
Simultaneously prepare all marketing and communication materials (ie: event posters, event landing page, key messaging, social media posts) for:
Our next big team event and;
Our next business development campaign;
Create a high quality and customized sales presentation in Google Slides by directing our graphic designers and incorporating input from our technical consultants;
Assume responsibility for all company social media channels and post high-quality, relevant, and diverse content at a frequency of once per week.
After 1 year you will be able to...
Own all current Marketing processes from start to finish;
Easily understand how to create a long-term marketing strategy which is in line with our company mission, vision, and strategy;
Spearhead and own any new initiative in our Growth strategy, and resourcefully align all the people and tools necessary to execute on it;
Use data to iterate on our company newsletter, blogs, thought leadership etc. and find new avenues to distribute the material broadly and frequently;
Expand your role into other areas of the company, providing unsolicited and valuable support for Software Development, Service Delivery, and People Ops, in addition to the Growth Team.
YOUR QUALIFICATIONS
Need to haves
3+ years related marketing experience;
Significant creative and technical writing skills with a strong command of the English language;
Ability to oversee content production by coordinating multiple resources (people), making quick decisions, and giving/taking honest feedback;
Imagination and creativity to be a self-starter, and commitment to maintain a laser focus on a specific objective when required;
Experience executing on best practices in digital communications and social media;
Hands-on experience with WordPress (or a similar CMS);
Pinpoint accuracy and attention to detail - we need to know EXACTLY where that piece of spinach in our teeth is;
A can-do attitude.
Nice to Haves
Experience working with government and the public sector or experience in a consulting environment;
Experience working in an Agile environment;
Understanding of best practices in account-based marketing;
Experience with Canva for creating digital media;
Working knowledge of the Adobe Creative Suite;
Some experience with HTML and CSS (even if it was a while ago);
Familiarity with our commonly used software or a similar alternative (eg: Slack, HubSpot, Jira, Trello, GSuite products);
Significant graphic design or video production chops;
Advanced experience with SEO, Google Analytics, and Search Console;
Event management experience.
